                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12712147" author="junrao" created="Fri, 22 May 2009 16:11:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;To fix the ordering of the returned result, we can reverse the returned list just before returning the thrift call, if the order is descending.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In terms of I/O, it is always better to fetch a group of columns from SSTable (instead of a column at a time). We can think about deserielizing a column at a time from the buffer. Doing this for descending order is bit difficult, but may still be possible.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12712160" author="jbellis" created="Fri, 22 May 2009 16:48:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, we can add a bandaid there, but &quot;iterate in descending order, to add to a sortedset in ascending order, to reverse before sending back to the client&quot; isn&apos;t exactly awesome.  In general exposing an API that looks to the public like it is low-cost but is really relatively high-cost is a bad idea.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(Yes, we should always do buffered reads, which is why I specifically said we want to &lt;em&gt;deserialize&lt;/em&gt; one at a time&quot; &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12728340" author="sandeep_tata" created="Tue, 7 Jul 2009 20:13:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;System test for descending slices.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12733343" author="junrao" created="Mon, 20 Jul 2009 20:33:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attache a patch, including a fix + the system test that Sandeep added.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12733616" author="jbellis" created="Tue, 21 Jul 2009 13:32:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks!  Can you rebase to trunk?  (Yep, I did try. &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12733682" author="junrao" created="Tue, 21 Jul 2009 16:11:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;attache patchv3. rebased to trunk.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12733864" author="jbellis" created="Tue, 21 Jul 2009 22:32:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;add(0) is a bad operation to do on a ArrayList, we should probably either use a deque or just do Collections.reverse at the end of the adds.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;other than that it looks fine to me.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;can you add a test slicing super subcolumns too?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12734184" author="junrao" created="Wed, 22 Jul 2009 16:32:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attache patch v4. Changed to collections.reverse and added a sc test. rebased to trunk.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12734326" author="jbellis" created="Wed, 22 Jul 2009 21:14:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;committed&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
